name: D҉i҉s҉i҉n҉t҉e҉g҉r҉a҉t҉e҉
description:
dis·​in·​te·​grate | \ (ˌ)dis-ˈin-tə-ˌgrāt

To break or decompose into constituent elements, parts, or small particles.
To undergo a change in composition.
To destroy the unity or integrity.

The urge to destroy is also a creative urge.
The urge to trascend beyond meaning is a must.

Single piece. Collection of one.
